    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Green pigment found in found in virtually all photosynthetic organisms, including plants and various green water-animalcules. It is involved in photosynthesis, which is the process by which light energy is converted to chemical energy through the synthesis of organic compounds: it absorbs energy from light; this energy is then used to convert carbon dioxide to carbohydrates. Pure chlorophyll appears as waxy dark green to black crystals. Chlorophyll has been used as a green colorant in clothing, soaps, leathers, waxes, foods, liquors, and perfumes. It is also used as a sensitizer for color film and as a deodorizer.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
